This method first caches any locally defined result in `self._associatedRst`. If not found, it traverses the parent tree recursively until a suitable definition is encountered.

```python
def _getAssociatedRst(self):
        """
        If interface has associated rst(_n) return it otherwise
        try to find rst(_n) on parent recursively
        """
        a = self._associatedRst

        if a is not None:
            return a

        p = self._parent
        assert p is not None

        if isinstance(p, UnitBase):
            return getRst(p)
        else:
            return p._getAssociatedRst()
```

The function prioritizes the local cache but relies on recursive calls if no association is found higher up in the tree.
